metry x="828" y="271" width="366" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Living in&lt;br&gt;a simulation&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+8+13+14+16]&lt;br&gt;→ ALLFED&lt;br&gt;   838k lives-eq/$1k · 70% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up AI safety (Redwood Research) · 16%&lt;br&gt;(Nick Bostrom)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + collapse_degrades_future + time_of_perils_exit + living_in_simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If most observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused → 13 collapse_degrades_future → 14 time_of_perils_exit → 16 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWWtv2zgW%2FSsXwc6u3U0cyW8nmwHSxpkpNn0gSXcwaAqXlmibG1nUklIcT6fz2%2FeQlGw5VlC3%2FlK4EnXuuec%2BeMl8OQj5hGVR%2BkqG%2FODk4PiYzs7O6FYxEVMqKVDsjyV%2BLGK6y5qe36aFVFH4IPiCFv6oOeqMuqP%2ByG%2BN%2FPbI71JNpzIhv1s3MHcx4M61zuZJKmRMwQyoJ%2BRRwpQMZoJFBtQfNMmnCVMjtmDL0Sybs1gXL5rEYjFnkR5pOeeLGUuLNx2aZGmmeP7BaM7SlKvRQqSzUSh0ILM4FfG0WN6lWJafjza%2BLlb1SWeTCVd2gQwyzcMVxRYFMopYovko5FPFQq5zkNWSNqVizkdyMkqAAdL8UawIQ51IPBhkEY%2B0mGcRM6pYkYYsmBFbKyU0MXq%2FTGf4PRERJ0Rj%2FVofU2qUYGGoD0lxhFDEXJNUFkzxIwjM5hx6CI3n6Yw77f%2BhIVocWIxTuDNPpDYarRbg2zjkQMQjoS2aTlkcskjGnObIkahBn1cpMHz4bKiaz%2FljwoMUHz6wKOMkJxZhnS0NC%2FaS65TG2ZIyY8Z8qHnZsRM6v7q6HF641b8M3w6vz2%2BHFzRe0pTHXLGUN5JlkYo8hLplWV7g5SECnTrjRjkgWawPccBValycS4XEWymk3VrnPkuSSHDdoJvlvBHJaSwVkq%2F2JekcUjLofK1bLBudgfcTvXp9aleOecrc00TJMRuLSKQgMpbGzdDU0UfvkPxPDb