+5+6+8+13+16+17]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;   73 lives-eq/$1k · 99% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up ALLFED · 1%&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + collapse_degrades_future + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused → 13 collapse_degrades_future → 16 living_in_simulation → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWWtT20gW%2FSu3qJ1dmwEj%2BW1nmSoCZia1JEMB2ampkHLaUtvuRVJruyWMN5P89j3dkmwZi4oTf0k5Uve5577vFZ8PfD5laZCcS58fDA9OTuj09JTuFBMRJZI8xf63xI9FRPdp03HbtJAq8B8FX9DCHTfHnXF33B%2B7rbHbHbs9qulExuT26gbmPgLcmdZpGCdCRuTNgTokh2KmpDcXLDCg7qBJLk2ZGrMFW47nacgiXbxoEotEyAI91jLkizlLijcdmqZJqnh%2BYRyyJOFqvBDJfOwL7ck0SkQ0K453KZLl5%2BON28WpPul0OuXKHpBeqrm%2FotgiTwYBizUf%2B3ymmM91DrI60qVAPJq7IhprEaYBs3oXr3sUc6VlNGaQ4VkWxpDWTCPmzYmtbSU0MbpeJnP8noqAE%2Fyxfq1PKDG2YL6vj0hxOFFEXJNUFkzxY5iYhRwWERrPkznPrP8PDbNFnsV4BYXCWGpjpdUB3I18DkQ8Etqi6YRFPgtkxClElAQN%2BrQKgtHjJ0PVXOdPMZTCxUcWpJzk1CKs46VhwV5zndAkXVJqxJiLmpcVG9IdsH4zXuF0xdks5dnFX0fvRjdnd6MLmixpxiOuWMIb8bKIS%2B6LZMNCh3h5BK8nGQ9jRCBZrPeRx1VitA2lQhSujKWzs5klWBwHgusG3S7DRiBnkVSIxNrnuHNE8aDzpW6xrKMGzk90%2FuaVPT